Ukraine stated that it is ready for negotiations with the Russian Federation on an ongoing basis
26 February 2022, 03:20
Photo: ©
Depositphotos
Read ren.tv in
Ukraine is completely open to negotiations with Russia. This was stated by the country's permanent representative to the UN, Sergei Kislitsa, during a meeting of the Security Council.
"We remain open to negotiations"
, - emphasized Kislitsa.
According to him, Kyiv’s position on this matter is always presented incorrectly. The permanent representative added that Ukraine is ready for negotiations “on an ongoing basis.”
"We always say this"
, he concluded.
Earlier, the press secretary of the President of Ukraine Sergei Nikiforov said that Kiev and Moscow
started discussion
time and place of negotiations. In addition, he denied claims that Ukraine had refused negotiations. Nikiforov noted that Kiev was and remains ready to discuss a ceasefire.
Earlier, Maria Zakharova, official representative of the Russian Foreign Ministry, stated that Kiev
refused negotiations
with Moscow. According to her, representatives of Ukraine proposed to postpone this issue to February 26.
Let us remind you that on February 21, Vladimir Putin announced his decision to recognize the independence of the Donetsk and Lugansk People’s Republics.
Later, on the morning of February 24, he announced the start of a military special operation to protect Donbass. The Ministry of Defense emphasized that there is no threat to Ukrainian civilians, because military strikes are targeted at Ukrainian military infrastructure.
